'''Anthony Hanson''' is a [[United Kingdom|British]] [[Master of Wine]]<ref>[http://www.mastersofwine.org/en/meet-the-masters/profile/index.cfm/id/efaea043-5e4b-e211-a20600155d6d822c Masters of Wine, Anthony Hanson profile]</ref> and a senior consultant to [[Christie's]] International Wine Department, as well as an expert on [[Burgundy (wine)|Burgundy]],<ref name= deca1/> an international [[wine]] judge and author.<ref>[http://www.christies.com/departments/wine-61-1.aspx Specialist Departments: Wine]</ref> His book ''Burgundy'' was first published in 1982, and since reissued in 2003.<ref name=wd-hans>{{Cite web|last= Kissack |first= Chris, thewinedoctor.com|title= Wine Books: Anthony Hanson |url= http://www.thewinedoctor.com/otherresources/hanson.shtml }}</ref> Following its initial publication, the book gained notoriety in part due to the famous description, "Great Burgundy smells of shit", a sentence which was modified in later editions.<ref>Atkin, Tim, ''The Observer'' (February 9, 2003). [https://www.theguardian.com/lifeandstyle/2003/feb/09/foodanddrink.shopping7 Something stinks...]</ref>

Hanson has also contributed to publications such as ''[[Decanter (magazine)|Decanter]]''<ref name= deca1>Hanson, Anthony, MW, ''Decanter.com'' (August 19, 2009). [http://www.decanter.com/features/burgundy-domaines-246657/ Burgundy: Domaines]</ref> and ''[[The World of Fine Wine]]''.

