'''Georgina Jolibois''' {{post-nominals|country=CAN|MP}} (born 1968) is a [[Canadians|Canadian]] politician, who was elected to represent the [[electoral district (Canada)|riding]] of [[Desnethé—Missinippi—Churchill River]] in the [[House of Commons of Canada]] in the [[Canadian federal election, 2015]].<ref>[http://globalnews.ca/news/2287506/ndps-georgina-jolibois-wins-in-desnethe-missinippi-churchill-river/ "NDP’s Georgina Jolibois wins in Desnethé-Missinippi-Churchill River"]. [[Global News]], October 20, 2015.</ref>

Prior to her election Jolibois served for twelve years as mayor of [[La Loche]].<ref>[http://thestarphoenix.com/news/crime/it-could-have-happened-anywhere-local-mp-says-la-loche-will-heal "'It could have happened anywhere': Local MP says La Loche will heal"]. ''[[Saskatoon Star-Phoenix]]'', January 28, 2016.</ref> She also served nine years on the [[Royal Canadian Mounted Police]] "F" Division’s Aboriginal Advisory Committee, working with law enforcement and other community partners to build safer communities in the North.

Jolibois sponsored the private member bill [http://www.parl.ca/DocumentViewer/en/42-1/bill/C-369/first-reading C-369] which sought to make [[National Indigenous Peoples Day]] a legal holiday.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/saskatchewan/bill-national-indigenous-peoples-day-stat-holiday-1.4379221 |publisher= CBC News |title=Bill proposing National Indigenous Peoples Day be a stat holiday is moving forward |accessdate=March 20, 2018 |date= October 30, 2017}}</ref>

