'''Leo Schaya''' (1916–1985) was a Swiss [[author]] and [[scholar]] whose works focused on the [[Sufi]] tradition, the [[Kabbalah]], and the [[Traditionalist School]].
==Biography== Born in [[Switzerland]], Schaya lived much of his adult life in [[Nancy, France]]. He grew up in a traditional Jewish household and from his early youth he was interested in the works of [[neo-Platonism]], [[Sufism]] and [[Advaita Vedanta]].
He published several articles on the [[Kabbalah]]. He also wrote a book on the [[Sufi]] doctrine of unity. He is the founder of the journal [[:fr:Connaissance des religions|''Connaissance des religions'' (''Knowledge of Religions'')]].
==Traditionalism== Schaya was a friend and frequent correspondent of prominent [[Traditionalist School|Traditionalist]] [[Frithjof Schuon]].
{{cquote|"The essential principles of the various orthodox revelations are identical, a fact which can be discovered by metaphysical penetration of dogmas and symbols."|20px|20px |Schaya on the Perennial Philosophy"<ref>Leo Schaya, The Universal Meaning of the Kabbalah ([[Penguin Books]], 1973) 10.</ref>}} <ref>(fr)[http://www.persee.fr/doc/rhr_0035-1423_1979_num_195_2_6882?q=%22Leo%20Schaya%22 Léo Schaya, "L'homme et l'absolu selon la Kabbale"]</ref> <ref>[https://books.google.fr/books?id=ojqcQf92M5YC&pg=PA87&dq=%22L%C3%A9o+Schaya%22&hl=fr&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwjtyqWGuvbTAhWE1xQKHWdwBHo4ChDoAQgiMAA#v=onepage&q=%22L%C3%A9o%20Schaya%22&f=false] "Pray Without Ceasing: The Way of the Invocation in World Religions", [[Patrick Laude]]</ref> <ref>[https://books.google.fr/books?id=Yb7jMKPi0WoC&pg=PA241&dq=%22L%C3%A9o+Schaya%22&hl=fr&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwjtyqWGuvbTAhWE1xQKHWdwBHo4ChDoAQgoMAE#v=onepage&q=%22L%C3%A9o%20Schaya%22&f=false] "Seeing God Everywhere: Essays on Nature and the Sacred" Barry McDonald, p. 241</ref> <ref>[https://books.google.fr/books?id=_sX2NCjoXNcC&pg=PA92&dq=%22L%C3%A9o+Schaya%22&hl=fr&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwjtyqWGuvbTAhWE1xQKHWdwBHo4ChDoAQgvMAI#v=onepage&q=%22L%C3%A9o%20Schaya%22&f=false] "La onzième heure: la crise spirituelle du monde moderne à la lumière ...", [[Martin Lings]], Pages 92, 93, 94</ref> <ref>(fr)[https://books.google.fr/books?id=O2-4xK7THisC&pg=PA68&dq=%22L%C3%A9o+Schaya%22&hl=fr&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwjtyqWGuvbTAhWE1xQKHWdwBHo4ChDoAQg1MAM#v=onepage&q=%22L%C3%A9o%20Schaya%22&f=false] "Le monde à l'envers: essais critiques sur la civilisation moderne" , [[Jean Hani]]</ref> <ref>[https://books.google.fr/books?id=KrUtBgAAQBAJ&pg=PA188&dq=%22L%C3%A9o+Schaya%22&hl=fr&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwiW5aCpqvbTAhWFbRQKHbN8BxsQ6AEIRzAG#v=onepage&q=%22L%C3%A9o%20Schaya%22&f=false Universal Aspects of the Kabbalah & Judaism, Leo Schaya]</ref> <ref>(fr)[https://books.google.fr/books?id=u4D9AwAAQBAJ&pg=PT462&dq=%22L%C3%A9o+Schaya%22&hl=fr&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwiW5aCpqvbTAhWFbRQKHbN8BxsQ6AEI