{{Orphan|date=March 2016}}
'''Thomas William Barker''' (1861&ndash;1912) was a [[Carmarthenshire]] solicitor, and Registrar of the Diocese of [[St David's]]. His father, J. H. Barker, was also a solicitor, and they worked together as partners of the firm Barker, Morris, and Barker.<ref name="DWB" />

In 1897 Thomas was appointed Secretary to the [[Bishop of St David's]], and in 1899 was appointed Registrar of the Diocese of St. David's, remaining in the position until his death in 1912.
<ref name="DWB">{{cite web|title=Thomas William Barker|url=http://yba.llgc.org.uk/en/s-BARK-WIL-1861.html|author=Griffith Milwyn Griffiths|year=1959|website=Dictionary of Welsh Biography|publisher=National Library of Wales|accessdate=8 March 2016}}</ref>

